From: John Cyrill Corsanes <4709030+jcchikikomori@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 11:31:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add missing X11 include for EGL builds

When USING_EGL is defined, SDLGLGraphicsContext.cpp calls XOpenDisplay()
and XCloseDisplay() and uses the Display type, but the required
<X11/Xlib.h> header is never explicitly included. On most platforms this
works because X11 headers are pulled in transitively through other
includes, but on some configurations (aarch64 Flatpak builds with GCC 15)
this fails.

Guard the include to avoid breaking Apple (where X11 may not be available
as a header) and FBDEV (which doesn't use X11 at all).

diff --git a/SDL/SDLGLGraphicsContext.cpp b/SDL/SDLGLGraphicsContext.cpp
index 1f61167ca..4ab55d9aa 100644
--- a/SDL/SDLGLGraphicsContext.cpp
+++ b/SDL/SDLGLGraphicsContext.cpp
@@ -15,6 +15,9 @@
 
 #if defined(USING_EGL)
 #include "EGL/egl.h"
+#if !defined(USING_FBDEV) && !defined(__APPLE__)
+#include <X11/Xlib.h>
+#endif
 #endif
 
 class GLRenderManager;
